  "text": "The MLE estimate can be determined by exploiting the non-linear optimization algorithms. The basic principle behind non-linear optimization is to find the optimal parameters so that log-likelihood function is maximized [CITATION_1] . This can be achieved by dividing the multi-dimensional parameter space into smaller sub-sets and applying trial and error approach such that for next iteration parameters value is modified so that it leads to better performance than that for previous parameters values.",
